# Resolution 2014-07-07.mzh.1: The Mana World (TMW) as an associated project

This resolution was adopted by the Board of Directors of SPI at their
meeting of [July 10th, 2014](/meetings/minutes/2014/2014-07-10/).

WHEREAS

1. The Mana World (TMW) is a community based innovative free and open
   source Massively Multiplayer Online Role-Playing Game (MMORPG) and is a
   substantial and significant Free Software project.  TMW promotes and
   increases the use of Open Source Software systems available to the general
   public and supports, encourages and promotes the creation and porting of
   its software to new architectures available to the general public.

2. The TMW developers would like SPI's support and assistance,
   including legal assistance, holding property and taking donations.

THE SPI BOARD RESOLVES THAT

3. The Mana World is formally invited to become an SPI Associated Project,
   according to the SPI Framework for Associated Projects, SPI Resolution
   1998-11-16.iwj.1-amended-2004-08-10.iwj.1, a copy of which can be found at
   [http://www.spi-inc.org/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1/](/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1/)

4. Ben Longbons is recognised by SPI as the authoritative decision maker
   and SPI liaison for TMW.  In the event that Ben Longbons is
   uncontactable, Edward Ivan Pasek will take over as SPI liaison.  Future
   liaisons will be appointed in turn by the sitting project liaison, or by
   a simple majority of existing TMW Committee members, as defined in
   [https://forums.themanaworld.org/viewtopic.php?f=1&t=17166](https://forums.themanaworld.org/viewtopic.php?f=1&t=17166)

5. This invitation will lapse, if not accepted, 60 days after it is
   approved by the SPI Board.

